Here’s how Ink To You works:

1.  Choose a printing plan based on the number of pages you expect to print in a month.
2.  When you enroll, a set of ink cartridges is shipped to you. Your service starts when the special Ink To You cartridges are inserted in your printer. If you enroll with the free trial offered during printer setup, your service will start as soon as you enroll and your free months will be in use.
3.  You will be billed at the end of your billing cycle each month after your service starts. Instant Ink monitors your usage and automatically ships cartridges before you need them – which means you won’t run out, but might not receive ink every month. Shipping and cartridge recycling is included with your service.
4.  If you print less than your plan amount, unused pages roll over (except the 15 page plan, which doesn’t include rollovers). If you print over your plan amount, additional pages will be added to your monthly bill at an affordable rate.
5.  Upgrade, downgrade, or cancel your service at any time with no extra fees or penalties. Because Instant Ink cartridges are connected to the service, the cartridges only work while your plan is active.

Read the following requirements to use the Ink To You service.

*   **Eligible Ink To You**: Go to [Ink To You](https://instantink.hpconnected.com/), and then scroll down to the FAQ section for a list of eligible printers.
*   **Active Internet connection to the printer**: The printer must be set up on a wired or wireless network and its Web Services feature turned on for Ink To You to know when to send you ink. USB cable-connected printers cannot connect to the service.
*   **Email address (Gmail, Yahoo Mail, Hotmail, etc.)**: Required as part of the enrollment. Do not use your printer’s ePrint email address.
*   **Valid credit or debit card**: A list of accepted credit and debit cards displays during enrollment.
*   **Supported countries**: Click the flag icon in the top right corner of the Ink To You website see if the service is available in your country.
